            "<p><strong>Problem 4.3</strong></p><p><strong>Genetic Traits: Finding any Percent</strong></p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "ETE_vM9dqhu5sWsw",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Have you ever heard of <em>genes</em>? (Not the &quot;jeans&quot; you wear, even though they sound the same.) What color are your eyes? Is your hair curly? Are your earlobes attached? We are born with a unique set of genes that help to determine these traits.</p><p>Scientists who student human traits such as eye and hair color are <em>geneticists</em>. Geneticists are interested in how common certain human traits are.</p><p>         <em>Look at the earlobe of a classmate. Is it attached or detached?</em></p><p>The type of earlobe we have is a trait determined partly by your genes. Here is a description of four genetic traits:</p>"
          ]
        }
